---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import {
  SNAPSHOTS,
  TARGET_DIDS,
  TARGET_YEAR,
  MISSION_STATEMENT,
  latest,
  progressPct,
  yearsRemaining,
  requiredAnnualMultiplier,
} from '../data/ssi-progress';

const current = latest();
const pct = progressPct(current);
const years = yearsRemaining();
const multiplier = requiredAnnualMultiplier(current);

function fmt(n: number): string {
  return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US').format(n);
}

function fmtMonth(iso: string): string {
  const [y, m] = iso.split('-');
  const date = new Date(Number(y), Number(m) - 1, 1);
  return date.toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long' });
}
---

<Base
  title="2034: Bring SSI to 100 Million"
  description="My personal mission: bring self-sovereign identity to 100 million people by 2034. Live progress."
>
  <h1>2034</h1>
  <p class="lede" style="font-size: 1.25rem; color: var(--color-muted); margin-bottom: 2.5rem;">
    {MISSION_STATEMENT}
  </p>

  <section class="ssi-counter">
    <div class="ssi-big">
      <span class="ssi-now">{fmt(current.totalDIDs)}</span>
      <span class="ssi-target">of {fmt(TARGET_DIDS)} DIDs</span>
    </div>
    <div class="ssi-bar" aria-label={`Progress: ${pct.toFixed(4)}%`}>
      <div class="ssi-bar-fill" style={`width: ${Math.max(pct, 0.05)}%`}></div>
    </div>
    <p class="ssi-meta">
      <strong>{pct.toFixed(4)}%</strong> of the way there ·
      <strong>{years} years</strong> remaining ·
      need to compound at <strong>{multiplier.toFixed(2)}×/year</strong>
    </p>
    <p class="ssi-asof">
      Source: OCME registry. Last verified <strong>{fmtMonth(current.month)}</strong>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <h2>Current snapshot — {fmtMonth(current.month)}</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Metric</th>
        <th style="text-align: right;">Value</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td>Members</td><td style="text-align: right;">{fmt(current.members)}</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Content pieces</td><td style="text-align: right;">{fmt(current.contentPieces)}</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Total DIDs</td><td style="text-align: right;"><strong>{fmt(current.totalDIDs)}</strong></td></tr>
      <tr><td>DID multiplier (DIDs per member)</td><td style="text-align: right;">{current.multiplier.toFixed(1)}×</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>DID breakdown</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Type</th>
        <th style="text-align: right;">Count</th>
        <th>Notes</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {current.breakdown.map((item) => (
        <tr>
          <td>{item.type}</td>
          <td style="text-align: right;">{fmt(item.count)}</td>
          <td>{item.notes ?? ''}</td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Why this number</h2>

  <p>
    Self-sovereign identity (SSI) is the missing trust layer of the digital world.
    Cryptographically secure, tamper-evident identity that the person — not the platform — controls.
    Without it, every digital interaction inherits the trust deficit of whoever is running the
    intermediating server.
  </p>

  <p>
    100 million is the threshold where SSI stops being a niche standard and starts being
    infrastructure people expect. It's roughly 1 in 80 humans alive today. That's not enough
    to be everyone — it's enough to make "you can have your own identity" the default expectation
    instead of a curiosity.
  </p>

  <p>
    2034 is ten years out from when I committed to the goal. Long enough to compound. Short enough
    that I have to act every quarter. The math says we need to roughly triple year-over-year for the
    next decade, which is hard but not unprecedented for infrastructure that crosses the chasm.
  </p>

  <h2>How we get there</h2>

  <p>
    Through <a href="/projects/open-commercial-media-ecosystem/">OCME</a>, primarily. Every member
    of the ecosystem mints a DID. Every piece of content gets DIDs. Every play, every payment, every
    showrunner agreement adds DIDs to the registry. The multiplier per member matters as much as the
    member count — currently ~25× per member, climbing as we ship new DID types
    (revenue receipts, playlists, license records).
  </p>

  <p>
    Adjacent levers: the <a href="/projects/trust-over-ip/">Trust Over IP Foundation</a> standards
    work, partnerships that bring entire creator cohorts in at once
    (Soulscape ~200, Guild ~2,000, Gato ~600), and any DID-issuing application built on top of the
    same infrastructure.
  </p>

  <h2>History</h2>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Month</th>
        <th style="text-align: right;">Members</th>
        <th style="text-align: right;">Total DIDs</th>
        <th style="text-align: right;">Multiplier</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      {[...SNAPSHOTS].reverse().map((s) => (
        <tr>
          <td>{fmtMonth(s.month)}</td>
          <td style="text-align: right;">{fmt(s.members)}</td>
          <td style="text-align: right;">{fmt(s.totalDIDs)}</td>
          <td style="text-align: right;">{s.multiplier.toFixed(1)}×</td>
        </tr>
      ))}
    </tbody>
  </table>

</Base>

<style>
  .ssi-counter {
    margin: 2.5rem 0;
    padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--color-code-bg);
  }
  .ssi-big {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .ssi-now {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  }
  .ssi-target {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
  }
  .ssi-bar {
    height: 12px;
    background: var(--color-rule);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin: 1rem 0 1.25rem;
  }
  .ssi-bar-fill {
    height: 100%;
    background: var(--color-accent);
    transition: width 600ms ease-out;
  }
  .ssi-meta,
  .ssi-asof {
    text-align: center;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    margin: 0.25rem 0;
  }
  .ssi-asof {
    color: var(--color-muted);
    font-size: 0.82rem;
  }
</style>
